  {
    "reference": "dialog.IDD_EXPR_WIZ_FILEHASH.caption",
    "text": "File Hash",
  },
  {
    "reference": "dialog.IDD_EXPR_WIZ_FILEHASH.1",
    "text": "File Hashing generates a fixed length unique identifier for each file based on the contents of the file. Files with identical contents will produce identical hash values.",
  },
  {
    "reference": "dialog.IDD_EXPR_WIZ_FILEHASH.2",
    "text": "1. Specify the hash algorithms in the Configuration settings",
  },
  {
    "reference": "dialog.IDD_EXPR_WIZ_FILEHASH.3",
    "text": "To search by hash value:",
  },
  {
    "reference": "dialog.IDD_EXPR_WIZ_FILEHASH.4",
    "text": "2. Enter the hash value to search for as either a comma separated list of hash values or a pointer to a list of hash values, e.g.",
  },
  {
    "reference": "dialog.IDD_EXPR_WIZ_FILEHASH.5",
    "text": "12EB0C408189C7870C83F0879B7C71AA,77116AB1664F3F85515F55F64506F848",
  },
  {
    "reference": "dialog.IDD_EXPR_WIZ_FILEHASH.6",
    "text": "=c:\hashfile.txt",
  },
  {
    "reference": "dialog.IDD_EXPR_WIZ_FILEHASH.7",
    "text": "OR,",
  },
  {
    "reference": "dialog.IDD_EXPR_WIZ_BOOLEANREGEX.caption",
    "text": "Boolean RegEx Engine",
  },
  {
    "reference": "dialog.IDD_EXPR_WIZ_BOOLEANREGEX.1",
    "text": "Boolean RegEx expressions are a hybrid of Boolean and Regular Expressions. Regular expressions can be combined using the familiar boolean operators AND, OR, and NOT.",
  },
  {
    "reference": "dialog.IDD_EXPR_WIZ_BOOLEANREGEX.2",
    "text": "Examples:",
  },
  {
    "reference": "dialog.IDD_EXPR_WIZ_BOOLEANREGEX.3",
    "text": ""doc.*[0-9]+" AND "author"",
  },
  {
    "reference": "dialog.IDD_EXPR_WIZ_BOOLEANREGEX.4",
    "text": ""error (120|121|123)" OR "info 344" NOT "archive"",
  },
  {
    "reference": "dialog.IDD_EXPR_WIZ_BOOLEANREGEX.5",
    "text": "Note: Use parentheses to group expressions, e.g. (work AND doc) OR (special AND case)",
  },
  {
    "reference": "dialog.IDD_EXPR_WIZ_WHOLEWORD.caption",
    "text": "Whole Word",
  },
  {
    "reference": "dialog.IDD_EXPR_WIZ_WHOLEWORD.1",
    "text": "Whole Word expressions are a similar to Boolean expressions except that each term only matches to exact words in the search text, i.e. excludes partial word matches. Terms can be combined using the familiar boolean operators AND, OR, and NOT",
  },
  {
    "reference": "dialog.IDD_EXPR_WIZ_WHOLEWORD.2",
    "text": "For example:",
  },
  {
    "reference": "dialog.IDD_EXPR_WIZ_WHOLEWORD.3",
    "text": "the author	searches for the specific words 'the' and 'author' excluding partial matches such as 'these' or 'authority'.",
  },
  {
    "reference": "dialog.IDD_EXPR_WIZ_WHOLEWORD.4",
    "text": "fish		matches against 'fish' but not 'fishing' or 'elfish'.",
  },
  {
    "reference": "dialog.IDD_EXPR_WIZ_FUZZY.caption",
    "text": "Fuzzy Search",
  },
  {
    "reference": "dialog.IDD_EXPR_WIZ_FUZZY.1",
    "text": "Fuzzy search expressions match the approximate search terms, in exactly the same way as the LIKE operator for Boolean Expressions. Since Fuzzy search expressions are a special type of Boolean expression individual search phrases can be combined using the AND, OR, and NOT operators.",
  },
  {
    "reference": "dialog.IDD_EXPR_WIZ_FUZZY.2",
    "text": "For example:",
  },
  {
    "reference": "dialog.IDD_EXPR_WIZ_FUZZY.3",
    "text": "separate	matches both separate and seperate but also separated and separately.",
  },
  {
    "reference": "dialog.IDD_EXPR_WIZ_FUZZY.4",
    "text": "collected	matches collected as well as collects and connected.",
  },
  {
    "reference": "dialog.IDD_EXPR_WIZ_MULTILINE_REGEX.caption",
    "text": "Multi-line Regex",
  },
  {
    "reference": "dialog.IDD_EXPR_WIZ_MULTILINE_REGEX.1",
    "text": "Multi-line regex matches regular expressions over multiple lines.",
  },
  {
    "reference": "dialog.IDD_EXPR_WIZ_MULTILINE_REGEX.2",
    "text": "For example:",
  },
  {
    "reference": "dialog.IDD_EXPR_WIZ_MULTILINE_REGEX.3",
    "text": ".{0,20}thought.{0,20}",
  },
  {
    "reference": "dialog.IDD_EXPR_WIZ_MULTILINE_REGEX.4",
    "text": "matches the word thought along with up-to 20 characters either side including characters on leading/trailing lines.",
  },
  {
